        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-11-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="269" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <head>No. 269.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Maury</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-11-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 14, 1887</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 44.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the views of the Department, as
                    expressed in its instruction No. 12, of the 25th February last, touching the
                    considerations which should operate to prevent the dependence of this and other
                    governments upon the mere courtesy of a private telegraph company on the isthmus
                    for the transmission of messages, I inclose<note n="*" xml:id="d269fn1">Inclosure not printed herewith.</note> a copy of a further complaint
                    against the Panama Railroad Company for its refusal to receive messages for
                    transmission across the isthmus.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
